<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-09-15T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-09-15T18:00:00-05:00" n="261" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d261">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/4130: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de
                                            Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-09-15T20:00:00-03:00">September 15, 1934—8
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 8:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>225. My 224. After further conversation this afternoon I am
                                authorized to say that despite irritation and concern Brazil is in
                                this mediation as long as [we?] desire her cooperation.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>